The paper discusses privacy in social networks and proposes methods to improve privacy through local cooperation. This topic falls under the category of computer security (cs.CR) and social and information networks (cs.SI). The paper also mentions the use of real-life social network topologies, which suggests a focus on data structures and algorithms (cs.DS) and databases (cs.DB). Additionally, the paper discusses the challenges of gathering enough individuals in distributed systems, which could fall under the category of social computing (cs.SOC).
